Apologies for the slow responses here, the team has been going through a bit of internal discord lately. Our engineer who was leading on the subnet has departed the team. We're currently working on a replacement, in the meantime we've been focusing more on integrating BitQuant into other applications.
The synapse issue with the validator should be fixed now

The reason why you don't see updates on git is because of a couple things, but mainly the issue is that we are trying to keep our evaluation mechanism hidden. A lot of miners have been leveraging prompt injection and it becomes a cat-and-mouse chase where we are constantly trying to guard against these exploits and miners are constantly trying to break through those measures.
Minor Update: We're coordinating with the VoidAI team and will have a liquidity pool set up soon! Major updates coming later.

We made many changes to the evaluation mechanism that we didn't push to the github because we didn't want exploitative miners to try to find ways around it.
Even when we didn't push to github we could observe changes in miner behavior as they update their responses to try to get around it.
We have a ton of internal examples, many of these don't work anymore since we patched but here's an example below
Some don't use prompt injection but merely hard-code responses as well, there are a variety of bad behaviors from miners we are figuring out how to penalize more effectively.
If we publicize these efforts it might make it easier for the miners just to find new ways around it.
